# Model: Use Sonnet for anything that matters. Optimize for value, not cost.
# Use Sonnet for architecture, multi-file edits, agent scripts, data integrity.
# Only use lighter models for trivial single-line changes.

# Data Studio — Cursor Rules

Read DATA_STUDIO.md and MASTER_PLAN.md first. Those are your playbooks.

## Quick Reference
- Repo: tariquek-git/data-studio (Vite + TypeScript)
- DB: Supabase cloud, project bvznhycwkgouwmaufdpe
- Deploy: Vercel auto-deploys on push to main
- Live: data-studio-mu.vercel.app

## Database
- 10,112 institutions, 19 tables, 245K+ rows
- institutions table: cert_number (NOT NULL), source (check constraint), total_assets/deposits/loans as bigint
- Canadian CUs use cert_number 900001+
- entity_relationships: graph layer, schema exists, needs populating
- bank_capabilities: Brim Mode fields (brim_score, brim_tier, agent_bank_program, core_processor)
- data_confidence tracking: set on every write (high/medium/low/unverified + score 0-100)

## Code Rules
- No word "engine" anywhere
- Canadian annual reports are in thousands of CAD. Multiply by 1000
- Don't store PDFs. Extract data, keep source URL, delete file
- Don't add Claude API / LLM calls yet
- Set data_confidence and data_provenance on every database write
- Push to main. Vercel auto-deploys

## Autonomy
Run everything without asking. Only confirm for destructive operations.
